text: I’m voting tonight to support the Pain-Capable Unborn Child Protection Act, which I cosponsored. Mississippi is one of 20 states with such a law on the books. #TheyFeelPain
Consider this: #SchumerShutdown would not only halt 6-yr CHIP extension, but also stop $1.48 billion in discretionary funding for Community Health Centers.
The thoughtful resolution of funding and priority issues will not be well served by a #SchumerShutdown. Let's work toward a budget agreement and get our work done.
2018!  Happy New Year, everyone!  God bless Mississippi and our great nation.
Merry Christmas! May you and yours have a safe and joyful holiday.
Happy Hanukkah! Best wishes to all beginning Festival of Lights celebrations tonight!

It’s a good thing when a sitting president visits Mississippi. Our state has done a great job on the Mississippi History & Civil Rights Museums, and I’m pleased @POTUS is interested in being part of our bicentennial celebration.
Congratulations to @GreggHarper, named chairman of the @HouseCommerce Subcommittee on Oversight and Investigations.  He’ll do great work for the American people.
North Korea missile launch underscores our need to increase defense and to reach a budget deal addressing our national security needs. Let’s find common ground on a budget deal. Soon.
As we gather with family and friends, let's be thankful for the blessings we enjoy as Americans. Have a safe & Happy Thanksgiving!
Happy 242nd birthday to the @USMC! Thank you for all you do to keep our country safe and free. Semper Fi.
There's no excusing the horror that occurred in Las Vegas. Let's unite to condemn this evil and pray for the victims and their families.
Thanks for the well-wishes. I'm not hospitalized, but am recuperating at home in Mississippi and look forward to returning to work soon.
Happy 70th birthday, @usairforce! Mississippi is proud of the brave men and women whose selflessness and service keep our country safe.
Voted tonight for the Countering America's Adversaries Through Sanctions Act to deter threats from North Korea, Iran & Russia. Passed 98-2.
Keep @SenJohnMcCain, Cindy, and his family in your thoughts and prayers. He's a fighter, and we hope to see him back in the Senate soon.
Deeply saddened by the loss of life in today's @USMC KC-130 crash in the Mississippi Delta. Our thoughts & prayers are w/everyone involved.
With Tropical Storm #Cindy in the Gulf, it's important to be prepared for inclement weather. Follow @MSEMA for updates.
Pleased @POTUS approved @FEMA disaster relief funds for Mississippi recovery after April 30 storms.
Our thoughts are w/Mississippians after deadly storms hit our state today. Follow @MSEMA & local authorizes as recovery work gets underway.
Enjoyed meeting w/Secretary of @USDOL nominee Alex Acosta today. Talked about important Miss. issues & will vote for confirmation tomorrow.
Happy Easter! May you and your family have a joyous and blessed day.
Thank you, @HailStateWBK, for an incredible season and representing our state so well. Mississippi is proud of all that you accomplished.
Wow, what a game! Congrats @HailStateWBK. We're proud of you!
Best of luck to @HailStateWBK as they take on UConn in the #NCAA Women's Final Four tonight!
Congrats @HailStateWBK and good luck in the Final Four! Mississippi is proud of you.
Congratulations to newly sworn-in U.S. Senator Luther Strange of Alabama. Look forward to working with you.
Voted tonight to confirm Jeff Sessions as Attorney General. I know he'll ensure our laws are enforced fairly and justly.
Pleased the Senate has confirmed Mike Pompeo for CIA director. We need to work swiftly to fill President Trump’s cabinet.
Our hearts go out to @Hattiesburg_MS & the Pine Belt after deadly tornado, severe storms. Appreciate @MSEMA coordinated disaster response.
ICYMI: Miss. House members gaining committee prominence. Looking forward to more good things from @GreggHarper @CongPalazzo @RepTrentKelly
Today is Law Enforcement Appreciation Day - a good reminder to thank those who risk their lives for our safety and security.
Enjoyed running into @mike_pence before our Senate GOP lunch in the Capitol. I look forward to working with him & the Trump administration.
May you and your family have a safe, happy, and prosperous 2017. Happy New Year!
Merry Christmas! I wish all Americans, and especially those serving overseas, a safe and joyful holiday.
Happy Hanukkah to all who are beginning celebrations tonight!

cc: @SenateDems
On the 75th anniversary of Pearl Harbor, we honor the men and women of the Greatest Generation  and their service to our country.
Pleased with the 99-0 Senate vote to extend #sanctions against Iran for 10 more years. Iran must be held accountable for its actions.
Today is #SmallBizSaturday! If you're holiday shopping, be sure to visit the local stores that make our Mississippi communities so unique.

Congratulations on your Hall of Fame induction, @Favre4Official! Mississippi is proud of you.
#FreedomIsntFree Disappointed Senate Democrats chose to block Defense Appropriations and put political posturing over funding our troops.
Happy birthday to the @USArmy, celebrating 241 years of defending  our freedom and liberty!
God bless all mothers - Happy Mother's Day!
Mississippi is proud of McComb's @laporsharenae & Amory's @TrentWHarmon, @AmericanIdol finalists carrying on our state’s rich music legacy.

Wishing you and yours a safe, joyful and very merry Christmas!

Happy Thanksgiving! In uncertain times, we can be especially thankful for our blessings as Americans and for those in uniform who protect us

Happy Independence Day! Thank you to the men and women serving in uniform to protect our rights and freedoms.

#239NavyBday. Happy Birthday to the @USNavy & thank you to all who have proudly served over the past 239 years.

#SBW2014 MS Small Business Person of the Year Bruce Patel of Fusion Hospitality in #Tupelo. Kudos to him & others for tornado recovery work.

Glad to have @USDA Sec. Vilsack's commitment to help Mississippi's farm, livestock & forestry sectors overcome #tornado disaster losses.

Pleased to have 10k followers. I enjoy hearing from & sharing w/Mississippians. We have a lot to be thankful for & to work toward together.
My thoughts and prayers are with Mayor Lumumba's family and friends, and the City of Jackson.

Wishing President George W. Bush a quick and full recovery. @GWBLibrary

Great game, @MSStateBB.  #HailStateCWS

Senate voting on #FarmBill passage. Bipartisan bill offers #agriculture producers certainty & also benefits consumers. Saves $24B.
The US Senate tonight passed The #StolenValor Act, HR258. Pleased to see this worthwhile legislation move forward. #Veterans

Senate #GunControl effort to create a new "assault weapons" ban fails, 40-60. I voted against resurrecting this failed policy. #Protect2A
Senate begins votes on #GunControl bill with the Manchin-Toomey background check proposal. I voted No. #Protect2A
I am concerned about the letter sent to my friend @SenatorWicker, and appreciate the work of law enforcement to resolve this situation.
Appreciate the efforts being undertaken to ensure public safety in #Boston. The thoughts & prayers of the nation are with those affected.
Enjoyed a visit today with the North American Agricultural Journalists to discuss ongoing work to reach consensus on a new Farm Bill.

Hotty Toddy! Go @OleMissMBB! #MarchMadness #NCAATournment
I just voted w/@SenTedCruz to #DefundObamacare. Congratulations to him on this effort. I continue to support full #Obamacare repeal.
Have asked FAA Administrator to consider negative effects on military before closing airport towers used by @DeptofDefense.  @JerryMoran
Pleased with the prompt federal disaster area designation for Miss. after tornadoes Sunday; @FEMA aid will help #Hattiesburg region rebuild.

Our hearts and prayers are with those touched by the evil violence today in Newtown, Conn.  It is a sad day for the entire nation.

As we gather together, let's thank our Armed Forces, veterans & everyone who works to make the USA better. Have a safe & Happy Thanksgiving.
Serving with Warren Rudman was an honor.  He will be well remembered for his wholehearted and tireless service to our nation.

Here's to wishing former Governor @HaleyBarbour a very happy birthday. Congratulations and best wishes, my good friend.

Pleased the federal emergency declaration sought by @PhilBryantMS has been approved. Makes @FEMA aid available to handle #Isaac damages.
